text: Ali Osman Ali was governor of Halabja Province in Iraq. Graduated from College of Law, University of Sulaimania, he was given the role of governor on 26 August 2016. He was replaced with Azad Tofiq in an internal deal by his governing PUK political party. == Citations == Category:Kurdish politicians Category:Governors of Halabja Governorate Category:University of Sulaymaniyah alumni Category:People from Kurdistan Province Category:Living people Category:Year of birth missing (living people)
